Sentencas: To examine the feasibility of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC)-powered unmanned undersea vehicle (UUV), a system level analysis is presented that projects a possible integration of the SOFC stack, fuel steam reformer, fuel/oxidant storage and balance of plant components into a 21-in.
Titulo: System modeling of an air-independent solid oxide fuel cell system for unmanned undersea vehicles
System modeling of an air-independent solid oxide fuel cell system for unmanned undersea vehicles

Sentencas: Heavy hydrocarbon fuel (dodecane) and liquid oxygen (LOX) are chosen as the preferred reactants.
Titulo: System modeling of an air-independent solid oxide fuel cell system for unmanned undersea vehicles

Sentencas: A maximum efficiency of 45% based on the lower heating value of dodecane was calculated for a system that provides 2.5 kW for 40 h. Heat sources and sinks have been coupled to show viable means of thermal management.
Titulo: System modeling of an air-independent solid oxide fuel cell system for unmanned undersea vehicles

Sentencas: The critical design issues involve proper recycling of exhaust steam from the fuel cell back into the reformer and effective use of the SOFC stack radiant heat for steam reformation of the hydrocarbon fuel.
Titulo: System modeling of an air-independent solid oxide fuel cell system for unmanned undersea vehicles
